window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>What doesn’t kill me had better start running.</b></p> <p>Life as I knew it ended with a bullet. It stole my brother from me and destroyed my family. From the ashes, I rose stronger and meaner, to exact the kind of revenge best served bloody and cold. I took out every single person I held responsible.</p> <p>Except one.</p> <p>He’s a phantom but his days are numbered. I won’t stop until I’m done.</p> <p>Then she shows up—the forbidden fruit, a light to my darkness. I should resist her because what I touch, I destroy. My feisty wildflower deserves more: more than this, more than me.</p> <p>But there is a monster lurking in the shadows. A psychopath watching her, watching us. His threats torment her and they make my black heart burn.</p> <p>He should know: you don’t ever mess with me or the people I love.</p> <p><i>Jack </i>is book one in the Kings of Mayhem MC Tennessee series. Contains mature content.</p>"; 
